The paper deals with algorithmic problems on subsets of Euclidean space, which suggests that it could belong to computational geometry (cs.CG) or data structures (cs.DS). The definition of fractal dimension used in the paper is related to measure theory and information theory, which could place it in those sub-categories (cs.IT and cs.NA, respectively). Finally, the paper also discusses approximation schemes and spanner constructions, which are topics commonly studied in theoretical computer science (cs.CC).
